subsection.p:
First, to address the issue of latency reduction, we provided in  an adaptive multi-flow routing algorithm to select end-to-end paths in packet-switched networks.
The algorithm is based only on local information, so it is suitable for distributed implementation;
furthermore, it provides guarantees that the network configuration converges to a stable state and exhibits several robustness properties that make it suitable for use in dynamic real-life networks (such as robustness to measurement errors, outdated information and update desynchronization).
